<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-06-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-06-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="73" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d73">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Denby</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Uhl</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-06-15"><hi rend="italic">June 15,
                                1895</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Riots still occurring in Szechuan. Mission at Chengtu not much damaged.
                            Have asked imperial edict awarding death penalty to rioters. Central
                            Government seems to have lost control over people. No American hurt.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Denby</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>